hook_method_def = Proc.new do |*args, &block|
            instance_method = hook_method.bind(self).to_proc
            call_instance_method = -> { instance_method.call(*args, &block) }

            # We may not have gotten the class for the method during
            # initialization (e.g. for a singleton method on an embedded
            # struct), so make sure we have it now.
            defined_class, = Hook.qualify_method_name(hook_method) unless defined_class

            reentrant = Thread.current[HOOK_DISABLE_KEY]
            disabled_by_shallow_flag = \
              -> { hook_package&.shallow? && AppMap.tracing.last_package_for_current_thread == hook_package }

            enabled = true if AppMap.tracing.enabled? && !reentrant && !disabled_by_shallow_flag.call

            return call_instance_method.call unless enabled

            call_event, start_time = with_disabled_hook.call do
              before_hook.call(self, defined_class, args)
            end
            return_value = nil
            exception = nil
            begin
              return_value = call_instance_method.call
            rescue
              exception = $ERROR_INFO
              raise
            ensure
              with_disabled_hook.call do
                after_hook.call(self, call_event, start_time, return_value, exception)
              end
            end
          end

children.name: request
children.comment:
# Sends an HTTPRequest object +req+ to the HTTP server.
#
# If +req+ is a Net::HTTP::Post or Net::HTTP::Put request containing
# data, the data is also sent. Providing data for a Net::HTTP::Head or
# Net::HTTP::Get request results in an ArgumentError.
#
# Returns an HTTPResponse object.
#
# When called with a block, passes an HTTPResponse object to the block.
# The body of the response will not have been read yet;
# the block can process it using HTTPResponse#read_body,
# if desired.
#
# This method never raises Net::* exceptions.
#
children.source:
def request(req, body = nil, &block)  # :yield: +response+
      unless started?
        start {
          req['connection'] ||= 'close'
          return request(req, body, &block)
        }
      end
      if proxy_user()
        req.proxy_basic_auth proxy_user(), proxy_pass() unless use_ssl?
      end
      req.set_body_internal body
      res = transport_request(req, &block)
      if sspi_auth?(res)
        sspi_auth(req)
        res = transport_request(req, &block)
      end
      res
    end

children.name: check_current_user
children.comment:
# check_current_user should always be called as a before_action. It will
# either pass through the request if anonymous access is allowed, or 
# require login and check the EULA.
children.source:
def check_current_user
    return true if anonymous_access? && !current_user?

    redirect_to_login unless current_user?

    true
  end

children.source:
def ensure_eula_accepted
    return true unless @current_user

    return true if @current_user.accept_eula?

    session[:return_to] = request.path if request.get?
    redirect_to license_path
  end

# with_authentication should always be called as an around_action.
# This method ensures that the label 'public' is applied if @current_user is falsey.
children.source:
def with_authentication(&block)
    if @current_user
      yield
    else
      with_anonymous_user(&block)
    end
  end

def list(login)
      DAO::ApiKey
        .where(login: login)
        .select(:id, :description, :last_used, :created_at)
        .order(Sequel.desc(:created_at))
        .all
        .map { |api_key| Show.new(api_key) }
    end

def revoke_from_user(login, key_id)
      DAO::ApiKey
        .where(login: login, id: key_id)
        .delete != 0
    end
